org.sabre.io.transport.http.data

Class HttpTransactionData

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sabre.io.transport.http.data.HttpTransactionData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TransactionData
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    HttpReqTransactionData, HttpRespTransactionData

    public class HttpTransactionData
extends java.lang.Object
implements TransactionData
    This is a container for the HTTP read and write transactions that are to be done. The same object is required to be put into the FlowContext against the appropriate key as follows : READ_REQ_DATA - The data read on an incoming HTTP Request Should contain headers and content. Can contain parameter map instead of content READ_RESP_DATA - On data read on an incoming HTTP response Should contain headers and content (optional) WRITE_REQ_DATA - The data that is required to be written out as a HTTP request Should contain headers. Can contain parameters or content or both (content is appended to the parameters) WRITE_RESP_DATA - The data that is required to be written out as a HTTP response Should contain headers and content (optional)
